		<div id="post_message_1246537">
                  
                  Sehra,<br />
I apologized because I didn't mean to upset you <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
I respect folk having the right to live, and die for their beliefs, but in this kind of case, it's just dumb, because it's based on a botched bit of several millenia-old writing....that's what's silly <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Frown" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
I call myself &quot;Christian&quot; because I believe Jesus was a holy prophet of God and the one I revere the most...doesn't mean I believe most of the malarky the Bible, and especially the religions, say. So, dying for a belief, makes sense, and I wouldn't deny an adult that right, provided it didn't harm another.<br />
But, as said, it's like dying for an arguement over an ancient, badly copied/translated/deliberately changed writing: extremely foolish.<br />
<br />
the Hygene laws of the Jewish faith were mostly very good practical things, as said. But folk *always* go totally nuts about such things and pervert the very intention of them by taking them to extremes, sigh.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
