Obedience to big G is one of the principles that could do that and would be universal across Judeo-Christian circles.  Look at the biblical example of Abraham and Isaac.  Look at the words in Isaiah about the suffering servant.  &quot;To obey is better than sacrifice&quot; is a key biblical principle.  <br />
<br />
What about wartime, defending your country or its ideals?  We expect people to go and fight, and risk their families.  What about firefighters?  They are needed desperately when a fire is ranging, but they also risk &quot;turning their children into orphans&quot;.  Same for police.  <br />
<br />
There is intent of the sort you are talking about all over the place in our culture.  I pity a culture that wouldn't have such principles, because it is destined for an everyone-for-themselves attitude that will lead to its own self-destruction.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
